[ Horse neighs ]

8
00:03:23,730 --> 00:03:26,000
THE GAME'S OVER!

9
00:03:31,440 --> 00:03:32,510
HERE SHE COMES.

10
00:03:32,610 --> 00:03:33,840
THAT'S
CALLIE CARPENTER?

11
00:03:33,940 --> 00:03:35,010
THE BOSS?

12
00:03:35,110 --> 00:03:38,010
SHE HATES
BEING CALLED THAT.

13
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:38,910
CALLIE!

14
00:03:39,010 --> 00:03:40,450
OVER HERE.

15
00:03:47,460 --> 00:03:49,590
CALLIE...LANE.

16
00:03:49,690 --> 00:03:51,890
LANE...CALLIE.

17
00:03:55,460 --> 00:03:56,660
LET'S GO.

18
00:03:56,770 --> 00:03:57,630
OK.

19
00:03:57,730 --> 00:03:59,130
YOU BOTH
KNOW THE RULES.

20
00:03:59,240 --> 00:04:01,740
YEAH,
THERE ARE NONE.

21
00:04:01,840 --> 00:04:04,340
NO PHYSICAL CONTACT
BETWEEN THE RIDERS.

22
00:04:04,440 --> 00:04:08,740
THE FIRST ONE
TO PASS RUDEBOY
BARRICADE WINS.

23
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:11,080
ON THE COUNT
OF THREE...

24
00:04:11,180 --> 00:04:12,810
ONE...

25
00:04:12,910 --> 00:04:14,310
TWO...

26
00:04:14,420 --> 00:04:15,350
THREE.

27
00:04:16,590 --> 00:04:17,650
CHEAP SHOT!

28
00:04:19,190 --> 00:04:21,720
TAKES WHAT IT TAKES,
BOSSY.

29
00:04:30,530 --> 00:04:33,700
[ Horns honking ]

30
00:05:00,230 --> 00:05:02,230
[ Heavy breathing ]

31
00:05:23,590 --> 00:05:24,780
HEY!

32
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,460
[ Truck horn blares ]

33
00:05:41,370 --> 00:05:44,270
[ Horns honking ]

34
00:05:44,370 --> 00:05:44,870
[ Crash ]

35
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:50,880
[ Bystander: ]
OH, WHAT HAPPENED?

36
00:05:50,980 --> 00:05:54,450
HEY,
WHAT DO YOU THINK
YOU'RE DOING, HUH?

37
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:58,720
CAN'T YOU LOOK
WHERE YOU'RE GOING?

38
00:05:58,820 --> 00:06:00,490
YOU COULD HAVE
KILLED SOMEBODY.

39
00:06:00,590 --> 00:06:02,320
LOOK AT MY BIKE,
MAN.

40
00:06:02,420 --> 00:06:03,990
WHERE'D YOU
LEARN TO DRIVE?

41
00:06:04,090 --> 00:06:05,320
AN AMUSEMENT PARK?

42
00:06:05,430 --> 00:06:06,890
[ Tires screeching ]

43
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:10,530
HEH HEH, YEAH!

44
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:39,760
HEY, CAL.

45
00:06:39,860 --> 00:06:42,400
WHAT'S UP
WITH THE BIKE?

46
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:44,400
OH, NOTHIN'.

47
00:06:49,670 --> 00:06:52,140
CAN I COME IN?

48
00:06:53,140 --> 00:06:54,770
CALLIE!

49
00:06:58,950 --> 00:07:00,880
[ Music from headphones ]

50
00:07:00,980 --> 00:07:02,250
CAL.

51
00:07:08,090 --> 00:07:12,930
YOU PROMISED
YOU WEREN'T GOING TO RACE
IN TRAFFIC ANYMORE.

52
00:07:13,030 --> 00:07:13,990
I WASN'T RACING.

53
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:15,800
YOU WERE RACING!

54
00:07:15,900 --> 00:07:17,630
AND YOU ARE LYING.

55
00:07:17,730 --> 00:07:21,070
I SAW
THE WHOLE THING.

56
00:07:21,170 --> 00:07:25,570
THESE KIDS
YOU'RE HANGING OUT WITH
AND THOSE STUPID STUNTS,

57
00:07:25,670 --> 00:07:27,770
I CAN'T STAND IT,
CALLIE.

58
00:07:27,880 --> 00:07:29,580
YOU COULD
HAVE BEEN HURT.

59
00:07:29,680 --> 00:07:31,110
YOU COULD
HAVE BEEN KILLED.

60
00:07:31,210 --> 00:07:34,450
CAN'T YOU EVER THINK
BEFORE YOU ACT?

61
00:07:34,550 --> 00:07:37,150
I WON'T DO IT
AGAIN.

62
00:07:37,250 --> 00:07:39,450
YEAH,
I'VE HEARD THAT BEFORE.

63
00:07:40,860 --> 00:07:43,420
WELL, I GUESS
IT DOESN'T MATTER NOW.

64
00:07:45,390 --> 00:07:47,290
MY GRANT WAS APPROVED.

65
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,830
WE'RE GOING
TO ENGLAND?

66
00:07:51,930 --> 00:07:53,930
CALLIE...

67
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:56,670
WELL, THAT'S COOL.

68
00:07:56,770 --> 00:07:58,970
THAT'S REALLY COOL.

69
00:07:59,980 --> 00:08:02,010
CALLIE, I'M GOING
TO ENGLAND...

70
00:08:02,110 --> 00:08:03,710
ALONE.

71
00:08:04,580 --> 00:08:05,180
WHAT?

72
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:07,080
I'M SORRY,
CAL.

73
00:08:07,180 --> 00:08:09,350
I WANTED
TO TAKE YOU WITH ME.

74
00:08:09,450 --> 00:08:10,550
I DID.

75
00:08:10,650 --> 00:08:14,090
I WAS LOOKING FORWARD
TO A SUMMER TOGETHER.

76
00:08:14,190 --> 00:08:17,920
BUT I CAN'T HAVE YOU
TEARING AROUND LONDON

77
00:08:18,030 --> 00:08:21,500
GETTING INTO CAB WRECKS,
RISKING YOUR LIFE.

78
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:22,760
I WON'T.
I SWEAR!

79
00:08:22,860 --> 00:08:25,500
THIS PROJECT
IS VERY INTENSE,

80
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:27,670
IF I DON'T PUBLISH
BY SEPTEMBER,

81
00:08:27,770 --> 00:08:29,740
I WON'T GET TENURE.

82
00:08:29,840 --> 00:08:30,800
YOUR STUPID JOB.

83
00:08:30,910 --> 00:08:33,210
THAT'S ALL
YOU CARE ABOUT.

84
00:08:39,450 --> 00:08:40,810
YOU KNOW WHAT?

85
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:41,780
IT'S FINE.

86
00:08:41,880 --> 00:08:42,880
THERE'S
NO WORRIES.

87
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:43,880
I'LL JUST...

88
00:08:43,990 --> 00:08:46,750
I'LL JUST
STAY HERE BY MYSELF.

89
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:49,390
I CAN'T LEAVE YOU ALONE
WHEN I'M HERE.

90
00:08:49,490 --> 00:08:51,490
I AM CERTAINLY NOT GOING
TO HAVE YOU

91
00:08:51,590 --> 00:08:54,160
BY YOURSELF
WHEN I'M GONE.

92
00:08:55,100 --> 00:08:57,430
OH, NO!

93
00:08:57,530 --> 00:08:59,930
NOT AUNT MAGGIE.

94
00:09:00,040 --> 00:09:02,070
AUNT MAGGIE?

95
00:09:02,170 --> 00:09:03,370
OLD McDONALD MAGGIE?

96
00:09:03,470 --> 00:09:04,700
E-I-E-I-O?

97
00:09:04,810 --> 00:09:06,870
NO, I'M SORRY.

98
00:09:06,980 --> 00:09:09,280
NOT IN THIS
LIFETIME.

99
00:09:09,380 --> 00:09:11,240
IT'S FOR THE BEST.

100
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:30,500
[ Cows mooing ]

101
00:09:43,410 --> 00:09:45,210
CALLIE,
YOU LIKE COWS?

102
00:09:45,310 --> 00:09:46,510
I DON'T EAT BEEF.

103
00:09:46,620 --> 00:09:48,620
OH, WELL,
HOW ABOUT HORSES?

104
00:09:48,720 --> 00:09:50,620
I PREFER CARS.

105
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:18,180
WELL, HERE WE ARE.

106
00:10:21,020 --> 00:10:22,650
CATCH.

107
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:25,990
I'LL GET SOMEONE TO HELP
WITH THE REST OF YOUR LUGGAGE.

108
00:10:26,150 --> 00:10:28,020
[ Horse whinnies ]

109
00:10:28,790 --> 00:10:31,520
[ Distant talking ]

110
00:10:36,730 --> 00:10:37,930
[ Whinnies ]

111
00:10:38,030 --> 00:10:39,070
WHOA!

112
00:10:39,170 --> 00:10:40,200
WHOA!

113
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:41,230
COME ON.

114
00:10:41,340 --> 00:10:43,200
COME ON,
COME ON, NOW.

115
00:10:43,300 --> 00:10:45,100
CALM DOWN.

116
00:10:45,210 --> 00:10:46,810
TURN AROUND.

117
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:48,040
THAT'S IT.

118
00:10:48,140 --> 00:10:50,840
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA!

119
00:10:54,450 --> 00:10:55,980
WHOA, BOY.

120
00:10:56,790 --> 00:10:57,980
EASY.

121
00:11:00,520 --> 00:11:02,060
WHOA.

122
00:11:03,360 --> 00:11:04,660
EASY, NOW.

123
00:11:05,760 --> 00:11:06,890
WHOA, BOY.

124
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,760
EASY.

125
00:11:09,870 --> 00:11:11,900
YEAH, THAT'S IT.

126
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,430
WHOA.

127
00:11:13,530 --> 00:11:15,300
STEADY.

128
00:11:15,400 --> 00:11:18,810
WHOA, BOY.

129
00:11:18,910 --> 00:11:20,840
EASY NOW.

130
00:11:21,940 --> 00:11:25,140
THAT'S IT.

131
00:11:25,250 --> 00:11:26,410
STEADY.

132
00:11:28,820 --> 00:11:31,080
RAFE, I TOLD YOU
BEFORE

133
00:11:31,190 --> 00:11:33,150
YOU'RE GONNA
GET YOURSELF KILLED.

134
00:11:33,250 --> 00:11:35,220
NOW STAY AWAY
FROM THAT HORSE!

135
00:11:43,630 --> 00:11:43,960
HEADS UP.

136
00:11:44,070 --> 00:11:46,070
AAUGH!

137
00:11:46,170 --> 00:11:48,270
GET THAT HORSE
OUT OF THERE.

138
00:11:48,370 --> 00:11:50,300
HEY,
WHAT'S GOING ON?

139
00:11:50,410 --> 00:11:51,540
OW!

140
00:11:52,410 --> 00:11:54,370
GET
MY HORSE, HERE.

141
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:55,410
SNAP, YOU ALL RIGHT?

142
00:11:55,510 --> 00:11:57,440
WHAT'S GOING ON
IN THERE?

143
00:11:57,550 --> 00:11:58,950
IT WAS THAT KID.

144
00:11:59,050 --> 00:12:00,680
HORSE WOULD HAVE
KILLED HIM.

145
00:12:00,780 --> 00:12:02,380
SNAPPER,
YOU ALL RIGHT?

146
00:12:02,480 --> 00:12:03,880
HE WAS
SETTLING DOWN.

147
00:12:03,990 --> 00:12:06,020
YOU STAY AWAY
FROM THAT ANIMAL.

148
00:12:06,120 --> 00:12:08,150
YOU KNOW
HOW DANGEROUS KIA CAN BE.

149
00:12:08,260 --> 00:12:12,060
HE'S OFF LIMITS TO EVERYONE,
EXCEPT SNAPPER.

150
00:12:12,160 --> 00:12:13,660
YOU UNDERSTAND?

151
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,400
YEAH.

152
00:12:18,230 --> 00:12:19,830
COME ON, NOW.

153
00:12:19,940 --> 00:12:21,500
GET THAT HORSE PUT UP.

154
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:24,040
GIVE ME A HAND
WITH SNAPPER HERE.

155
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:45,220
[ Mitchell: ]
I JUST DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT'S WRONG WITH KIA--

156
00:12:45,330 --> 00:12:47,490
SUCH GOOD BREEDING.

157
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:49,200
[ Snapper: ]
IT JUST DOESN'T FIGURE.

158
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:52,070
THAT HORSE
IS MAKING ZERO
PROGRESS, MITCHELL.

159
00:12:52,170 --> 00:12:53,930
HE'S A LOST CAUSE.

160
00:12:54,040 --> 00:12:55,630
HOW BAD
HE HURT YA?

161
00:12:55,740 --> 00:12:58,400
A FEW BRUISED RIBS,
MAYBE TWO BROKE.

162
00:12:58,510 --> 00:13:01,140
THAT HORSE COULD
KICK YA INTO NEXT WEEK.

163
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:04,240
THE VET THOUGHT HE MIGHT
HAVE ENCEPHALOMYELITIS,

164
00:13:04,350 --> 00:13:06,410
BUT THE TEST
CAME UP NEGATIVE.

165
00:13:06,510 --> 00:13:10,280
I THINK WE GOTTA SERIOUSLY
CONSIDER PUTTING HIM DOWN.

166
00:13:10,390 --> 00:13:13,690
WELL, I'M NOT READY
TO TAKE THAT STEP
JUST YET.

167
00:13:13,790 --> 00:13:15,650
FACE IT, MITCHELL.

168
00:13:15,760 --> 00:13:17,590
OUR BREEDIN' EXPERIMENT
DIDN'T WORK.

169
00:13:17,690 --> 00:13:21,190
WE PROBABLY CROSSED LINES TOO
CLOSE--GOT A MUTANT OFFSPRING.

170
00:13:21,300 --> 00:13:24,660
WE GOT A LOT OF MONEY
INVESTED IN THAT HORSE.
MITCHELL...

171
00:13:24,770 --> 00:13:26,730
CONTINUE
TRAINING HIM.

172
00:13:26,840 --> 00:13:27,970
THAT'S WHY
I BROUGHT YOU HERE.

173
00:13:28,070 --> 00:13:29,640
[ Clears throat ]

174
00:13:33,540 --> 00:13:37,780
YEAH, THEY'RE
JUST BEAUTIFUL,
AREN'T THEY?

175
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:40,610
I WANT
TO BE STRAIGHT
WITH YOU, CALLIE.

176
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:43,220
WHEN YOUR AUNT MAGGIE
INVITED YOU HERE,

177
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:46,690
I WASN'T SURE
WHAT WE WERE GETTING INTO.

178
00:13:46,790 --> 00:13:48,890
I SURE DIDN'T ASK
TO COME.

179
00:13:48,990 --> 00:13:49,960
WELL, I KNOW.

180
00:13:50,060 --> 00:13:52,460
BUT YOU'RE HERE AND
THAT'S A PLAIN FACT.

181
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:56,200
BUT, WELL,
JUST SO THERE'S NO
MISUNDERSTANDINGS,

182
00:13:56,300 --> 00:13:58,430
I THINK
WE SHOULD GET THINGS
CLEAR BETWEEN US,

183
00:13:58,530 --> 00:14:00,470
YOU KNOW, RIGHT
AT THE BEGINNING.

184
00:14:00,570 --> 00:14:02,600
YEAH,
LIKE WHAT?

185
00:14:02,700 --> 00:14:07,010
WELL, EVERYONE PULLS
HIS WEIGHT AROUND HERE.

186
00:14:07,110 --> 00:14:09,710
THERE'S A LOT OF WORK
ON A RANCH,

187
00:14:09,810 --> 00:14:11,810
AND I'M GOING
TO GIVE SOME TO YOU.

188
00:14:11,910 --> 00:14:15,780
I'VE ASKED RAFE
TO TEACH YOU TO RIDE,

189
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:17,780
DO SOME CHORES...

190
00:14:17,890 --> 00:14:21,150
MEET HIM IN THE HORSE
BARN IN THE MORNING.

191
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:22,820
HE'LL BE WAITING.

192
00:14:22,920 --> 00:14:24,920
RAFE...

193
00:14:25,030 --> 00:14:27,630
THE GUY WHO TRIED
TO CALM THE HORSE?

194
00:14:27,730 --> 00:14:29,260
THAT'S HIM.

195
00:14:32,370 --> 00:14:34,270
WHAT'S WITH
THAT BLACK HORSE?

196
00:14:34,370 --> 00:14:36,540
OH,
THAT'S A LONG STORY.

197
00:14:55,790 --> 00:14:57,490
WHAT TOOK YA
SO LONG?

198
00:15:00,160 --> 00:15:02,160
DANGEROUS FOR ME
TO BE AWAY.

199
00:15:02,260 --> 00:15:03,800
SOMEONE AT THE
RANCH MIGHT NOTICE.

200
00:15:03,900 --> 00:15:05,460
THAT'S YOUR PROBLEM.

201
00:15:06,870 --> 00:15:08,800
MR. WELLS
WANTS TO KNOW

202
00:15:08,900 --> 00:15:12,340
WHEN HE CAN TAKE DELIVERY
OF HIS HORSE?
SOON.

203
00:15:15,640 --> 00:15:18,080
FOSTER'S NOT READY
TO GIVE UP, YET.

204
00:15:18,180 --> 00:15:19,750
THEN STEAL IT.

205
00:15:19,850 --> 00:15:21,110
WHAT ARE YOU,
CRAZY?

206
00:15:21,220 --> 00:15:22,180
YOU CAN'T DO THAT.

207
00:15:22,280 --> 00:15:24,320
IT'S TOO EASY
TO TRACE.

208
00:15:24,420 --> 00:15:27,190
WELLS HAS
TO BE PATIENT

209
00:15:27,290 --> 00:15:29,460
AND FOLLOW THE
ORIGINAL PLAN.

210
00:15:33,630 --> 00:15:36,960
MR. WELLS IS NOT
A PATIENT MAN.

211
00:15:51,950 --> 00:15:53,880
SO, WHAT IS YOUR STORY?

212
00:16:14,470 --> 00:16:16,400
HI,
YOU MUST BE CALLIE.

213
00:16:16,500 --> 00:16:20,040
MITCHELL SAID
YOU'RE SUPPOSED
TO TEACH ME SOMETHING.

214
00:16:23,040 --> 00:16:25,180
NICE TO MEET YOU, TOO.

215
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:38,390
LESSON ONE
IS WHAT COWBOYS CALL
JUICIN' THE COW.

216
00:16:38,490 --> 00:16:40,060
JUICIN' THE COW?

217
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:41,890
HERE, PUT THIS ON.

218
00:16:44,330 --> 00:16:46,700
I NEED A HAT
TO MILK A COW?

219
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:47,630
TRUST ME.

220
00:16:47,740 --> 00:16:50,770
IT KEEPS THE COW'S HAIR
OR WHATEVER

221
00:16:50,870 --> 00:16:52,810
FROM GETTING
IN YOUR HAIR.

222
00:16:52,910 --> 00:16:53,870
GROSS.

223
00:16:53,970 --> 00:16:56,780
NOW, GRAB THE BUCKET
IN YOUR RIGHT HAND

224
00:16:56,880 --> 00:16:59,680
AND STOOL IN YOUR LEFT
AND COME HERE.

225
00:16:59,780 --> 00:17:01,250
WHAT'S HER NAME,
ANYWAY?

226
00:17:01,350 --> 00:17:03,520
CALLIE,
MEET BOSSY.

227
00:17:04,520 --> 00:17:06,050
[ Moos ]

228
00:17:06,150 --> 00:17:10,190
PUT YOUR FOOT HERE
IN THE STIRRUP, AND THEN...

229
00:17:12,490 --> 00:17:14,960
GOT IT?

230
00:17:15,060 --> 00:17:16,800
NOW, YOU TRY.

231
00:17:21,570 --> 00:17:23,370
UHH.

232
00:17:30,210 --> 00:17:33,850
THERE'S A REASON
NOT TO WEAR THOSE
KIND OF SHOES.

233
00:17:33,950 --> 00:17:36,420
HERE,
LET ME HELP YOU.

234
00:17:40,590 --> 00:17:42,220
[ Grunts ]

235
00:18:00,110 --> 00:18:01,610
[ Man: ]
MR. WELLS IS CONCERNED

236
00:18:01,710 --> 00:18:04,410
YOU MIGHT BE TRYING
TO DELIVER DAMAGED MERCHANDISE.

237
00:18:04,510 --> 00:18:06,750
[ Snapper: ]
THERE'S NOTHING
WRONG WITH THE HORSE.

238
00:18:06,850 --> 00:18:08,680
A LOT OF TIME
AND MONEY

239
00:18:08,780 --> 00:18:11,020
WENT INTO SELECTING
A MARE AND SIRE,

240
00:18:11,120 --> 00:18:15,020
BOTH WERE STRONG
BAR D AND SWING RANCH
BLOODLINES.

241
00:18:15,120 --> 00:18:16,490
WITH THAT BLOODLINE,

242
00:18:16,590 --> 00:18:19,830
HE'S POTENTIALLY ONE
OF THE FINEST STUDS
IN THE COUNTRY.

243
00:18:19,930 --> 00:18:22,060
AS LONG AS YOU
CAN DELIVER.

244
00:18:51,390 --> 00:18:53,360
I KNOW A HUSTLE
WHEN I SEE ONE.

245
00:18:53,460 --> 00:18:55,260
I MEAN,
ON THE ONE HAND,

246
00:18:55,360 --> 00:18:57,860
HE'S TELLING
THIS GUY THAT KIA'S
A GREAT HORSE,

247
00:18:57,970 --> 00:18:59,500
AND ON
THE OTHER HAND,

248
00:18:59,600 --> 00:19:03,070
HE'S TRYING
TO CONVINCE MITCHELL
TO DESTROY HIM.

249
00:19:03,170 --> 00:19:06,510
I'LL TELL YOU ONE THING
ABOUT THAT HORSE.

250
00:19:06,610 --> 00:19:11,180
I COULD SETTLE HIM DOWN IF
SNAPPER'D GIVE ME A CHANCE.

251
00:19:11,280 --> 00:19:13,350
RAFE,
THIS IS SERIOUS.

252
00:19:13,450 --> 00:19:15,910
SOMETHING'S GOING ON
AND IT'S NOT RIGHT.

253
00:19:27,760 --> 00:19:29,090
THANKS.

254
00:19:38,070 --> 00:19:40,170
LET'S GET BACK
TO WORK.

255
00:19:44,680 --> 00:19:47,710
I FEEL LIKE A PRISONER
ON A CHAIN GANG.

256
00:19:47,820 --> 00:19:50,550
YOU LOOK
LIKE ONE, TOO.

257
00:19:56,290 --> 00:19:57,890
EASY, KIA.

258
00:19:57,990 --> 00:20:00,460
WHOA, BOY.

259
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:03,800
YOU GONNA SOLVE
ALL MY PROBLEMS?

260
00:20:03,900 --> 00:20:05,630
STEADY, BOY.

261
00:20:09,140 --> 00:20:11,440
THAT OUGHTA DO IT.

262
00:20:11,540 --> 00:20:13,410
[ Laughs ]

263
00:20:13,970 --> 00:20:16,480
THAT REALLY
OUGHTA DO IT.

264
00:20:16,580 --> 00:20:18,540
[ Laughs ]

265
00:20:20,450 --> 00:20:23,220
GET WILD, BOY,
GET WILD!

266
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:24,450
[ Laughs ]

267
00:20:26,750 --> 00:20:30,290
[ Neighing ]

268
00:20:30,990 --> 00:20:32,830
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

269
00:20:32,930 --> 00:20:35,130
HE SHOULDN'T BE DOING THIS.

270
00:20:35,230 --> 00:20:37,030
IT'S NOT WORTH IT,
MITCHELL.

271
00:20:37,130 --> 00:20:38,530
HE SHOULD
BE PUT DOWN.

272
00:20:38,630 --> 00:20:40,230
BEFORE YOU DO THAT,
MITCHELL,

273
00:20:40,340 --> 00:20:42,740
LISTEN TO WHAT
CALLIE HAS TO SAY.

274
00:20:42,840 --> 00:20:45,800
LAST NIGHT,
HE GAVE KIA A SHOT

275
00:20:45,910 --> 00:20:48,110
THAT MADE
HIM WILD.

276
00:20:48,210 --> 00:20:51,440
WHAT'S SHE TALKING
ABOUT, SNAPPER?

277
00:20:51,550 --> 00:20:55,210
JUST DOING WHAT THE VET
TOLD ME TO DO.

278
00:20:55,320 --> 00:20:57,820
I GIVE HIM
VALIUM EVERY NIGHT.

279
00:20:57,920 --> 00:20:59,720
TO KEEP HIM
UNDER CONTROL.

280
00:20:59,820 --> 00:21:02,260
HOW COME HE GOT
SO CRAZY, THEN?

281
00:21:02,360 --> 00:21:05,020
VALIUM HADN'T
TAKEN EFFECT,
I GUESS.

282
00:21:05,130 --> 00:21:07,530
MAGGIE, SNAPPER KNOWS
WHAT HE'S DOING.

283
00:21:07,630 --> 00:21:10,330
YOU GOT ENOUGH
PROBLEMS OF YOUR OWN

284
00:21:10,430 --> 00:21:12,330
WITHOUT GETTING
INVOLVED

285
00:21:12,430 --> 00:21:14,970
WITH SOMETHING
YOU KNOW NOTHING ABOUT.

286
00:21:15,070 --> 00:21:17,370
YOU OWE SNAPPER,
HERE, AN APOLOGY.

287
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,010
CALLIE...

288
00:21:29,120 --> 00:21:30,220
[ Sighs ]

289
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:31,950
SORRY, SNAPPER.

290
00:21:32,050 --> 00:21:34,020
AHHH, DON'T THINK
ABOUT IT.

291
00:21:34,120 --> 00:21:36,120
KIDS ARE LIKE THAT.

292
00:21:36,220 --> 00:21:38,220
NOW THE REAL
QUESTION...

293
00:21:38,330 --> 00:21:40,060
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO
ABOUT THE HORSE?

294
00:21:40,160 --> 00:21:42,960
I GUESS THERE'S NO
REAL CHOICE, IS THERE?

295
00:21:43,060 --> 00:21:46,230
SURE DON'T WANT HIM
TO HURT SOMEBODY ELSE.

296
00:21:46,330 --> 00:21:47,400
OF COURSE NOT.

297
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:50,300
MITCHELL,
YOU BRED THAT HORSE
TO BE A CHAMPION.

298
00:21:50,410 --> 00:21:51,640
DON'T
GIVE UP ON HIM.

299
00:21:51,740 --> 00:21:52,670
LOOK AT HIM.

300
00:21:52,770 --> 00:21:55,640
MAGGIE, I GOT A FORTUNE
SUNK IN THAT HORSE.

301
00:21:55,740 --> 00:21:59,750
YOU THINK
I WANT TO SEE THAT
ALL GO DOWN THE DRAIN?

302
00:22:02,020 --> 00:22:03,280
CALL THE VET.

303
00:22:03,380 --> 00:22:04,820
MAKE THE ARRANGEMENTS.

304
00:22:31,710 --> 00:22:33,450
[ Snorts ]

305
00:22:44,220 --> 00:22:45,520
HMMM...

306
00:22:51,300 --> 00:22:52,930
COME ON.

307
00:22:55,740 --> 00:22:57,240
OH, COME ON.

308
00:22:58,540 --> 00:22:59,810
HERE YOU GO.

309
00:23:00,610 --> 00:23:01,670
COME ON.

310
00:23:12,450 --> 00:23:13,590
YEAH.

311
00:23:13,690 --> 00:23:15,450
ALL RIGHT.
GOOD BOY.

312
00:23:22,430 --> 00:23:25,700
YOU'RE STILL TEACHING ME
HOW TO DO STUFF, RIGHT?

313
00:23:25,800 --> 00:23:27,300
RIGHT.

314
00:23:27,400 --> 00:23:30,070
WELL, THIS IS
THE MORNING FEED.

315
00:23:37,980 --> 00:23:39,110
THAT'S ALL THEY GET.

316
00:23:39,210 --> 00:23:42,280
THEY'LL EAT
THE WHOLE BARREL
IF YOU LET THEM.

317
00:23:42,380 --> 00:23:43,550
SO?

318
00:23:43,650 --> 00:23:46,050
THE OATS LIE
IN THEIR STOMACH,

319
00:23:46,150 --> 00:23:50,590
THEY CAN GET COLIC,
AND THEY CAN DIE.

320
00:23:51,390 --> 00:23:52,630
BUMMER.

321
00:23:54,090 --> 00:23:56,190
SO, HAVE YOU THOUGHT
OF A PLAN YET?

322
00:23:56,300 --> 00:23:57,930
A PLAN?

323
00:23:58,030 --> 00:23:59,670
YEAH, A PLAN.

324
00:23:59,770 --> 00:24:01,500
TO SAVE KIA.

325
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:03,040
TO SAVE KIA?

326
00:24:04,470 --> 00:24:06,470
IS THERE AN ECHO
OUT HERE?

327
00:24:07,340 --> 00:24:08,470
AN ECHO?

328
00:24:10,310 --> 00:24:13,110
SNAPPER HAS CONVINCED
MITCHELL TO PUT KIA DOWN.

329
00:24:13,210 --> 00:24:14,310
WHEN?

330
00:24:14,410 --> 00:24:15,250
I DON'T KNOW.

331
00:24:15,350 --> 00:24:17,580
HE WENT OFF
TO CALL THE VET.

332
00:24:17,690 --> 00:24:19,820
SO HOW ABOUT THIS...

333
00:24:19,920 --> 00:24:22,390
WE STEAL KIA.

334
00:24:23,160 --> 00:24:24,990
NOT PERMANENTLY
OR ANYTHING.

335
00:24:25,090 --> 00:24:27,130
JUST FOR
A LITTLE WHILE.

336
00:24:27,230 --> 00:24:28,790
AND WE TRAIN HIM.

337
00:24:34,170 --> 00:24:37,900
YOU DO KNOW HOW TO TRAIN
A HORSE, DON'T YOU?

338
00:24:38,010 --> 00:24:39,240
YOU'RE NUTS.

339
00:24:39,340 --> 00:24:41,140
AND WHAT IS THIS
"WE" BUSINESS?

340
00:24:41,240 --> 00:24:42,580
I DON'T NEED
SOME CITY GIRL

341
00:24:42,680 --> 00:24:46,180
TELLING ME TO RISK MY JOB
TO STEAL MY BOSS'S STUD.

342
00:24:46,280 --> 00:24:50,720
THE ONLY THING
I CAN'T FIGURE OUT
IS WHERE TO HIDE HIM.

343
00:24:50,820 --> 00:24:54,250
BUT I'M SURE WITH ALL
THE YEARS YOU'VE LIVED HERE,

344
00:24:54,350 --> 00:24:56,620
YOU KNOW
OF A PLACE.

345
00:24:58,890 --> 00:25:00,730
COME ON, RAFE,
HELP ME.

346
00:25:00,830 --> 00:25:03,530
I COULD
GET IN TROUBLE.

347
00:25:03,630 --> 00:25:05,300
I NEED THIS JOB,
CALLIE.

348
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:06,870
BUT IT'LL WORK.

349
00:25:06,970 --> 00:25:08,370
WE CAN
MAKE IT WORK.

350
00:25:08,470 --> 00:25:10,440
YOU AND ME TOGETHER.

351
00:25:13,640 --> 00:25:14,640
I JUST CAN'T.

352
00:25:14,740 --> 00:25:15,640
WELL, I CAN

353
00:25:15,740 --> 00:25:18,310
AND I'M NOT LETTING HIM
KILL THAT HORSE.

354
00:25:18,410 --> 00:25:20,980
WHAT IS IT WITH YOU
AND THAT HORSE?

355
00:25:21,080 --> 00:25:23,320
SNAPPER'S A SNAKE
AND I DON'T TRUST HIM.

356
00:25:23,420 --> 00:25:26,650
SNAPPER IS ONE
OF THE BEST TRAINERS
IN THE COUNTRY.

357
00:25:26,750 --> 00:25:29,660
WHO WAS THAT CREEPY GUY
I SAW HIM WITH?

358
00:25:29,760 --> 00:25:30,990
SNAPPER LIKES
TO GAMBLE.

359
00:25:31,090 --> 00:25:33,330
IT WAS PROBABLY
SOMEONE FROM THE TRACK.

360
00:25:33,430 --> 00:25:37,100
IF YOU'RE NOT
GOING TO HELP ME,
I'LL DO IT MYSELF.

361
00:25:39,470 --> 00:25:43,840
LOOK, YOU'LL HAVE THE HORSE
SOON ENOUGH.

362
00:25:43,940 --> 00:25:46,300
HANG ON.

363
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:49,210
YOU WATER
THE FOALS YET?

364
00:25:49,310 --> 00:25:49,880
UH-HUH.

365
00:25:49,980 --> 00:25:51,210
GOOD.

366
00:25:53,550 --> 00:25:55,380
TAKE OFF, THEN.

367
00:25:55,480 --> 00:25:58,250
I GOT THINGS TO DO.

368
00:26:05,890 --> 00:26:06,860
I'M BACK.

369
00:26:08,960 --> 00:26:10,030
DON'T WORRY.

370
00:26:10,130 --> 00:26:11,200
LIKE I SAID,

371
00:26:11,300 --> 00:26:13,030
I'LL TAKE CARE
OF EVERYTHING.

372
00:26:13,130 --> 00:26:15,670
YOU'LL HAVE YOUR HORSE
SOON ENOUGH.

373
00:26:22,310 --> 00:26:23,740
[ Tapping ]

374
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:41,130
OK, YOU WIN.

375
00:26:41,230 --> 00:26:43,200
I KNOW A PLACE.

376
00:26:43,300 --> 00:26:46,230
MEET ME BEHIND THE STABLES
AT DAWN.

377
00:26:46,330 --> 00:26:49,670
IT WILL TAKE US AWHILE
TO RIDE UP THERE.

378
00:26:49,770 --> 00:26:51,070
RIDE?

379
00:26:52,270 --> 00:26:53,170
WAIT...

380
00:26:53,270 --> 00:26:54,170
ME?

381
00:27:00,780 --> 00:27:02,080
DAWN?

382
00:27:09,060 --> 00:27:11,060
HOW MUCH FURTHER
IS IT?

383
00:27:13,690 --> 00:27:16,230
DID YOU HAVE TO BRING
THIS STUPID BACKPACK?

384
00:27:22,900 --> 00:27:23,940
WOW!

385
00:28:20,530 --> 00:28:22,090
HERE WE ARE.

386
00:28:49,860 --> 00:28:52,960
MY FATHER
BROUGHT ME HERE
WHEN I WAS LITTLE.

387
00:28:53,060 --> 00:28:56,760
HE TOLD ME
THE ANCIENT ONES
LIVED HERE.

388
00:28:56,860 --> 00:29:00,700
LATER,
THE SHOSHONE USED IT
FOR SECRET MEETINGS.

389
00:29:00,800 --> 00:29:02,400
THEY WERE
COMPLETELY HIDDEN,

390
00:29:02,500 --> 00:29:04,640
BUT COULD SEE
ENEMIES APPROACHING

391
00:29:04,740 --> 00:29:06,570
FROM THE LOOKOUT POINT.

392
00:29:08,910 --> 00:29:11,110
DO YOU EVER
COME HERE ANYMORE?

393
00:29:15,450 --> 00:29:17,420
ONCE IN AWHILE,
YES.

394
00:29:17,520 --> 00:29:20,820
WHEN I NEED
TO BE ALONE.

395
00:29:20,920 --> 00:29:22,960
DOES ANYONE ELSE
KNOW ABOUT IT?

396
00:29:23,060 --> 00:29:26,320
NOBODY AT THE RANCH,
IF THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE THINKING.

397
00:29:26,430 --> 00:29:28,790
WE CAN KEEP KIA HERE
TIL HE'S TRAINED...

398
00:29:28,900 --> 00:29:30,860
IF HE CAN BE TRAINED.

399
00:29:32,470 --> 00:29:34,230
YAH, YAH!

400
00:29:34,330 --> 00:29:35,970
GET UP THERE.

401
00:29:36,070 --> 00:29:36,840
YAH!

402
00:29:36,940 --> 00:29:38,270
COME ON THERE.

403
00:29:38,370 --> 00:29:40,110
COME ON.

404
00:29:40,210 --> 00:29:42,040
YAH, YAH!

405
00:29:42,140 --> 00:29:43,740
YEAH, THAT'S IT.

406
00:29:43,840 --> 00:29:45,780
YOU'RE LOOKING GOOD,
RACHEL.

407
00:29:48,150 --> 00:29:49,110
THANKS, MAX.

408
00:29:52,920 --> 00:29:54,720
YAH, YAH!

409
00:29:56,960 --> 00:29:58,120
[ Neighs ]

410
00:29:58,760 --> 00:30:00,060
YAH!

411
00:30:07,200 --> 00:30:09,000
[ Clanking ]

412
00:30:13,040 --> 00:30:14,310
DARN IT!

413
00:30:18,210 --> 00:30:19,110
HUNGRY?

414
00:30:21,550 --> 00:30:23,320
I'M GOING
ON A PICNIC.

415
00:30:23,420 --> 00:30:24,420
WITH?

416
00:30:25,690 --> 00:30:27,150
MYSELF.

417
00:30:35,060 --> 00:30:37,860
THAT'S AN
AWFUL LOT OF APPLES
YOU GOT THERE.

418
00:30:37,970 --> 00:30:41,100
I MAY BE GONE
FOR A LONG TIME, SO...

419
00:30:43,670 --> 00:30:46,100
AREN'T YOU
FOSTER'S NIECE
FROM NEW YORK?

420
00:30:46,210 --> 00:30:47,270
THAT'S ME.

421
00:30:51,080 --> 00:30:53,580
WHAT'S IT LIKE
IN NEW YORK?

422
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:56,650
SOPHISTICATED.

423
00:31:11,830 --> 00:31:13,230
WELL...

424
00:31:13,330 --> 00:31:16,270
GEE WHIZ, YOU GUYS,
YOU KNOW...

425
00:31:16,370 --> 00:31:17,440
I'M JUST BUSHED,

426
00:31:17,540 --> 00:31:20,940
I THINK
I'M GOING TO HEAD OFF
AND GO TO SLEEP.

427
00:31:21,040 --> 00:31:22,740
GOOD NIGHT.

428
00:31:22,840 --> 00:31:25,140
GOOD NIGHT.
GOOD NIGHT.

429
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:45,400
COME ON.

430
00:31:45,500 --> 00:31:47,730
JUST LET ME TRY.
HE TRUSTS ME.

431
00:31:47,830 --> 00:31:50,200
WOULD YOU PLEASE
JUST BE QUIET.

432
00:31:50,300 --> 00:31:52,540
YOU'RE MESSING
EVERYTHING UP.

433
00:31:52,640 --> 00:31:55,140
DID ANYONE
EVER TELL YOU

434
00:31:55,240 --> 00:31:58,740
HOW NICE YOU'D BE
IF YOU'D JUST BE NICE?

435
00:32:07,420 --> 00:32:08,690
HEY, DOC.

436
00:32:10,360 --> 00:32:12,520
THANKS FOR COMIN'.

437
00:32:14,330 --> 00:32:17,460
WHY HAVEN'T I HEARD
FROM YOU BEFORE NOW?

438
00:32:17,560 --> 00:32:18,560
CUZ...

439
00:32:18,670 --> 00:32:21,000
EVERYTHING'S
BEEN FINE.

440
00:32:21,100 --> 00:32:24,170
THE VALIUM WORKS GREAT,
JUST LIKE YOU SAID.

441
00:32:24,270 --> 00:32:27,670
I OVERDOSE HIM
AND IT MAKES HIM
TOTALLY CRAZY.

442
00:32:27,770 --> 00:32:31,610
FOSTER REALLY BELIEVES
HE'S GOT A DEFECTIVE ANIMAL.

443
00:32:31,710 --> 00:32:34,080
WELLS' PEOPLE
VISITED ME THIS AFTERNOON.

444
00:32:34,180 --> 00:32:35,880
THEY'RE TIRED OF WAITING.

445
00:32:35,980 --> 00:32:37,880
THEY WANT
THAT HORSE, TONIGHT.

446
00:32:37,990 --> 00:32:40,390
THAT OUGHT TO WORK OUT
JUST PERFECT.

447
00:32:40,490 --> 00:32:42,520
FOSTER'S FINALLY DECIDED
TO DESTROY HIM.

448
00:32:42,620 --> 00:32:45,520
GLAD TO HEAR YOU FINALLY
GOT YOUR ACT TOGETHER.

449
00:32:45,630 --> 00:32:48,030
YOU BRING THE DOPE?

450
00:32:48,130 --> 00:32:49,360
BE CAREFUL WITH THIS.

451
00:32:49,460 --> 00:32:51,360
IT'S NOT VALIUM.

452
00:32:51,470 --> 00:32:53,370
YOU GIVE MORE THAN 100 CCs,

453
00:32:53,470 --> 00:32:56,730
YOU REALLY WILL HAVE
A DEAD HORSE ON YOUR HANDS.

454
00:33:01,980 --> 00:33:03,180
EASY, BOY.

455
00:33:04,210 --> 00:33:05,610
EASY, BOY.

456
00:33:05,710 --> 00:33:06,710
HURRY UP!

457
00:33:06,810 --> 00:33:08,180
I'M TRYING.

458
00:33:08,280 --> 00:33:09,980
LET ME TRY.

459
00:33:10,080 --> 00:33:12,250
NO,
YOU DON'T KNOW HOW.

460
00:33:14,220 --> 00:33:15,090
COME ON.

461
00:33:15,190 --> 00:33:16,590
EASY, KIA.

462
00:33:16,690 --> 00:33:19,720
YOU'RE NOT DOING
SO GREAT YOURSELF.

463
00:33:29,170 --> 00:33:29,900
HERE, BOY.

464
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:30,870
HERE.

465
00:33:33,610 --> 00:33:36,740
THINK NOBODY
EVER HEARD OF CARROTS
BEFORE YOU GOT HERE?

466
00:33:38,180 --> 00:33:40,110
HERE, KIA.

467
00:33:40,210 --> 00:33:41,650
GOOD BOY.

468
00:34:08,780 --> 00:34:12,940
SEE?
I TOLD YOU
I COULD GET HIM TO DO IT.

469
00:34:13,050 --> 00:34:15,150
SURPRISED YOU, HUH?

470
00:34:15,250 --> 00:34:18,150
GUESS I KNOW
MORE ABOUT HORSES
THAN YOU THINK.

471
00:34:18,250 --> 00:34:22,190
I THINK
WE SHOULD BE QUIET
FOR THE REST OF THE WAY.

472
00:34:22,290 --> 00:34:25,260
IT WON'T BE LONG
BEFORE THEY'LL
START LOOKING.

473
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:27,020
YOU'RE JEALOUS.

474
00:34:27,130 --> 00:34:29,660
NOPE,
JUST WORRIED.

475
00:34:37,370 --> 00:34:39,140
DID THEY FIND HIM?

476
00:34:39,240 --> 00:34:40,810
NOT A TRACE.

477
00:34:40,910 --> 00:34:43,010
MOST OF THE MEN
HAVE BEEN OUT
ALL NIGHT.

478
00:34:43,110 --> 00:34:45,140
WELL,
I HOPE HE'S NOT HURT.

479
00:34:45,250 --> 00:34:47,180
MAYBE WE SHOULD
OFFER A REWARD.

480
00:34:48,850 --> 00:34:50,120
OH,
YOU LOOK GREAT.

481
00:34:50,220 --> 00:34:51,550
LOOK AT HER,
MITCHELL.

482
00:34:51,650 --> 00:34:52,580
DOESN'T SHE
LOOK GOOD?

483
00:34:52,690 --> 00:34:54,420
GREAT.
WOW.

484
00:34:54,520 --> 00:34:56,550
EVERYTHING OK,
CALLIE?

485
00:34:56,660 --> 00:34:58,220
SURE, WHY?

486
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:04,930
HEY, WAIT UP.

487
00:35:05,030 --> 00:35:06,300
WHERE YOU GOIN'?

488
00:35:07,970 --> 00:35:09,230
TO MEET RAFE.

489
00:35:09,340 --> 00:35:12,470
MY, YOU TWO ARE
GETTING AWFULLY CLOSE.

490
00:35:12,570 --> 00:35:13,740
OH, YEAH.

491
00:35:13,840 --> 00:35:16,270
WE'RE ALREADY
TALKING ABOUT WHAT
TO NAME THE KIDS.

492
00:35:16,380 --> 00:35:17,610
VERY FUNNY.

493
00:35:17,710 --> 00:35:19,810
SO, WHAT
ARE YOU UP TO?

494
00:35:19,910 --> 00:35:21,010
AW, YOU KNOW...

495
00:35:21,120 --> 00:35:22,180
EXPLORING.

496
00:35:22,280 --> 00:35:23,320
LATER...

497
00:35:35,130 --> 00:35:37,730
HOW YOU DOING,
CALLIE?

498
00:35:37,830 --> 00:35:39,400
OH, FINE.

499
00:35:39,500 --> 00:35:41,900
SEEMS KIA BROKE OUT
OF HIS CORRAL.

500
00:35:42,000 --> 00:35:42,730
OH...

501
00:35:42,840 --> 00:35:43,870
FUNNY, THOUGH.

502
00:35:43,970 --> 00:35:46,540
